I just got                      

02:52.505 --> 02:53.772
 a call from <i>Redbook</i> magazine,  

02:53.840 --> 02:55.574
    and I have been selected    

02:55.642 --> 02:57.576
    as one of the six Boston    
         businesswomen          

02:57.644 --> 03:00.579
      to get a full beauty      
        makeover.               

03:00.647 --> 03:03.315
And the final results will      
    be in their next issue.     

03:03.383 --> 03:05.117
Oh, that's too bad.             

03:05.185 --> 03:06.785
I always liked                  
 <i>Redbook.</i>                       

03:08.188 --> 03:10.222
Rebecca, I can't possibly think 

03:10.290 --> 03:12.257
 why you would need a makeover. 

03:12.325 --> 03:13.625
You're always                   
impeccably dressed.             

03:13.693 --> 03:14.760
You're constantly               

03:14.828 --> 03:17.162
            alluring            
without being overstated.       

03:17.230 --> 03:19.164
Well, thank you, Frasier.       

03:19.232 --> 03:23.168
Your eye makeup gives you       
a certain feline quality.       

03:23.236 --> 03:25.170
    It's irresistible.          
                        Mm.     

03:25.238 --> 03:27.673
And I can't see how anyone      
     could possibly improve     

03:27.741 --> 03:29.675
 on the way your hair cascades  
         down your face         

03:29.743 --> 03:31.677
in that peekaboo fashion.       

03:31.745 --> 03:34.913
    Much like my own darling    
            Lilith.             

03:34.981 --> 03:38.150
             Speak of the devil!

03:38.218 --> 03:39.985
            Not that you're a   
            devil, of course.   

03:40.053 --> 03:41.987
                Just, uh, the   
                 total opposite.

03:42.055 --> 03:43.989
             In fact, you're the
            complete opposite   
                of the devil.   

03:44.057 --> 03:46.492
                    You're i.e.,
                    an angel.   

03:46.559 --> 03:49.161
There's no need                 
to be nervous, Frasier.         

03:49.229 --> 03:50.496
It's perfectly                  
natural for you                 

03:50.563 --> 03:52.164
to be attracted                 
to other women.                 

03:52.232 --> 03:54.833
It shows you have a,            
a healthy sex drive.            

03:54.901 --> 03:56.835
I'm attracted                   
to other men.                   

03:56.903 --> 03:58.971
                Oh, no, not this
                     game again.

03:59.039 --> 04:01.473
Let's see,                      
where shall I begin?            

04:04.811 --> 04:06.812
        Yowsa!                  

04:06.880 --> 04:08.947
So Miss Howe's gonna            
be in <i>Redbook.</i>                  

04:09.015 --> 04:10.115
Well, what is that?             

04:10.183 --> 04:11.383
Some kind of fashion            
magazine?                       

04:11.451 --> 04:12.618
          Oh, no, no.           

04:12.686 --> 04:15.487
 It's, uh, more than a fashion  
        magazine, Woody.        

04:15.555 --> 04:16.755
It, it's about                  
today's women.                  

04:16.822 --> 04:18.257
You know, who they are,         

04:18.324 --> 04:19.425
uh, their wants,                
their needs.                    

04:20.627 --> 04:21.827
Cliffie, you read <i>Redbook?</i>      

04:21.894 --> 04:23.796
I don't so much                 
as read it, Norm.               

04:23.863 --> 04:26.165
I, uh, I do take some           
of the quizzes, though.         

04:28.301 --> 04:29.601
Would you believe               

04:29.669 --> 04:32.004
that I'm actually               
autumn complected?              

04:32.072 --> 04:35.007
  Hey, guys, you're not gonna   
         believe this.          

04:35.075 --> 04:37.142
        Gary sold               
     The Olde Towne Tavern.     

04:37.210 --> 04:38.143
                             No!
            Get out!            

04:38.211 --> 04:39.144
SAM:                            
No kidding.                     

04:39.212 --> 04:40.979
        He sold it              
    to this guy named Frank.    

04:41.047 --> 04:42.915
Uh, runs a bunch of bars        
in other cities.                

04:42.982 --> 04:44.083
        He's already in.        

04:44.150 --> 04:45.317
                  Wait a minute.
                 This means that

04:45.385 --> 04:47.786
        any bar tab run         
 under the previous management  

04:47.854 --> 04:49.254
  would automatically be null   
        and void, right?        

04:49.322 --> 04:52.191
 You have a bar tab at Gary's?  

04:52.258 --> 04:53.692
    Not anymore, Sam.           

04:54.761 --> 04:57.863
          Oh, no more Gary's?   

04:57.931 --> 05:00.399
         I can't believe that!  

05:00.467 --> 05:02.401
             You know, in a way,
                I'm gonna really
                  miss that guy.

05:02.502 --> 05:03.669
Miss him?                       
You kidding me?                 
                        Yeah.   

05:03.737 --> 05:05.404
Worst thing                     
that ever happened to me.       

05:05.472 --> 05:07.306
I've never been happier         
to see a guy go.                

05:07.374 --> 05:08.574
            Aw, come on, Sam.   

05:08.641 --> 05:09.775
Nah, he was terrible.           

05:09.843 --> 05:10.909
He even turned                  
you guys,                       

05:10.977 --> 05:12.244
my good friends,                
against me.                     

05:12.312 --> 05:13.812
                     Huh?       
You remember                    
Halloween?                      

05:13.880 --> 05:14.880
                Oh.             
When you                        
convinced me                    

05:14.948 --> 05:15.948
that I killed                   
the man?                        

05:16.016 --> 05:17.850
Ha ha.                          
            (laughs)            

05:17.917 --> 05:21.020
        Yeah, you hate to see   
          the great ones retire.

05:21.087 --> 05:23.022
    Boy, without Gary,          
    what's left for us, huh?    

05:23.089 --> 05:25.457
So, huh,                        
what do you think?              

05:25.525 --> 05:27.893
You ready to start a rivalry    
with the, uh, new bar?          

05:27.961 --> 05:29.061
      What are you talking      
             about?             

05:29.129 --> 05:30.262
             Yeah.              
Come on.                        

05:30.330 --> 05:31.764
It's a golden opportunity.      

05:31.898 --> 05:33.298
We can win this time.           

05:33.366 --> 05:35.300
We can steal                    
all of Gary's best ideas        

05:35.368 --> 05:36.869
and use 'em                     
against this new guy.           

05:36.936 --> 05:38.704
And you remember how Gary's     
always going first?             

05:38.772 --> 05:39.872
We can learn                    
from that.                      

05:39.939 --> 05:41.874
We can move first               
ourselves.                      

05:41.941 --> 05:43.075
                 Very good, Sam.

05:43.143 --> 05:44.777
As that famous                  
prankster                       

05:44.844 --> 05:46.612
                    Santayana   
                      once said,

05:46.680 --> 05:48.447
            "Those who do not   
              learn from history

05:48.515 --> 05:49.948
                are condemned   
                  to repeat it."

05:50.016 --> 05:51.950
      You got that right,       
         Doctor Crane.          

05:52.018 --> 05:53.552
      Back in high school       
        I was condemned         

05:53.620 --> 05:55.554
 to repeat History three times. 

05:57.724 --> 05:59.958
By the way, the same goes       
        for Mathematics.        

06:01.795 --> 06:03.095
Come on, come on.               

06:03.163 --> 06:04.730
What do you say                 
we show this Frank guy          

06:04.798 --> 06:05.964
there's another bar             
in town?                        

06:06.032 --> 06:07.766
            Do we really want to
                let ourselves in

06:07.834 --> 06:09.134
                for that kind of
              humiliation again?

06:09.202 --> 06:11.570
      Sure!                     

06:11.638 --> 06:13.238
Oh, no, no, Sam,                
I think Normie's right.         

06:13.306 --> 06:14.840
I mean, if there's one thing    
Gary taught us                  

06:14.908 --> 06:17.643
it's that we're nothing         
but a bunch of losers.          

06:17.711 --> 06:19.945
Yeah, but the new guys          
don't know that.                

06:20.013 --> 06:21.747
Well, let's show 'em,           
         huh?                   

06:21.815 --> 06:23.749
                        Yeah!   

06:28.488 --> 06:31.090
                Okay, I'll be   
                     right back.

06:31.157 --> 06:32.424
                Okay.           
            (gasps)             

06:32.492 --> 06:34.093
             Look at me!        
         Lilith, look at me!    

06:34.160 --> 06:35.928
Isn't this                      
exciting?                       
                    Yes.        

06:35.995 --> 06:38.931
        Every so often people   
                need to recreate
                     themselves.

06:38.998 --> 06:41.934
              And frequently the
          metamorphosis has very
            positive results.   

06:42.002 --> 06:44.269
You should've seen              

06:44.337 --> 06:46.605
what I looked like              
back in my college days.        

06:46.673 --> 06:48.640
     Bowwow!                    

06:50.710 --> 06:52.978
So, Rebecca, you're having      
a makeover, huh?                

06:53.046 --> 06:54.313
                Yes.            

06:54.381 --> 06:56.281
You know, uh, I don't           
understand. I mean,             

06:56.349 --> 06:58.550
if there was ever a person      
  who didn't need a makeover,   

06:58.618 --> 06:59.818
        it's you.               

06:59.886 --> 07:01.453
     I think you're perfect     
     just the way you are.      

07:01.521 --> 07:04.023
Oh, well, thank you, Paul.      

07:04.090 --> 07:06.025
 Boobs, too, or just the face?  

07:09.696 --> 07:11.463
         Just the face.         

07:11.531 --> 07:13.499
              Eh.               

07:17.904 --> 07:19.838
        (Norm chuckles)         

07:21.775 --> 07:23.275
                 I assume you've
                    just come   

07:23.343 --> 07:25.010
            from the new Olde   
                Towne Tavern.   

07:25.078 --> 07:26.645
      Yeah, we went for an      
    often used stunt,           

07:26.713 --> 07:28.313
      but one that's sure       
    to bring a smile.           

07:28.381 --> 07:30.182
          (laughs)              
            We teepeed the whole
             front of the place.

07:30.250 --> 07:31.550
          And how will they know

07:31.618 --> 07:33.719
    that you're the dastardly   
